    "faq": [
      {
        "question": "What is the belt CLI?",
        "answer": "Belt is the command-line interface for inference.sh, a cloud platform that provides access to 250+ AI models for image generation, video creation, LLM queries, web search, and more."
      },
      {
        "question": "Do I need a GPU to run these AI models?",
        "answer": "No. All inference runs in the cloud on inference.sh infrastructure. You only need the belt CLI installed and an authenticated account."
      },
      {
        "question": "How do I authenticate with inference.sh?",
        "answer": "Run belt login after installation. This opens a browser for OAuth authentication. For CI/CD, you can set the INFSH_API_KEY environment variable instead."
      },
      {
        "question": "Can I use local files as input to AI models?",
        "answer": "Yes. The belt CLI automatically uploads local files when you provide a file path instead of a URL in the input JSON. Supported paths include absolute, relative, and home directory paths."
      },
      {
        "question": "How are AI model versions managed?",
        "answer": "Apps use the format namespace/app-name. You can pin to a specific version using namespace/app-name@version syntax for reproducible results across runs."
      },
      {
        "question": "Is there a free tier available?",
        "answer": "inference.sh offers free credits for new accounts. Usage beyond the free tier requires purchasing additional credits. Check inference.sh pricing for current rates."
      }
